## Design Tokens

Tokens are defined in `packages/design-system/src/tokens/` using the `--dxy-` prefix.

### Color Tokens

Colors are defined in oklch format. Each color has a base and faded variant.

| Token | Purpose | Faded Variant |
|-------|---------|---------------|
| `--dxy-color-primary` | Primary actions, links (Blue) | `--dxy-color-primary-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-secondary` | Secondary elements (Slate) | `--dxy-color-secondary-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-accent` | Highlights, accents (Violet) | `--dxy-color-accent-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-warning` | Warning states (Amber) | `--dxy-color-warning-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-positive` | Success states (Green) | `--dxy-color-positive-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-critical` | Error states, destructive actions (Red) | `--dxy-color-critical-faded` |
| `--dxy-color-neutral` | Placeholder, muted backgrounds (Light gray) | `--dxy-color-neutral-faded` |

### Spacing Tokens

